                    <mrow><mi mathvariant="-tex-caligraphic">D</mi></mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow>
            </msup>
        </math>
        and the new one
        <math>
            <msup>
                <mrow>
                    <mrow><mi mathvariant="-tex-caligraphic">D</mi></mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow>
            </msup>
        </math>
        . If we use
        <math>
            <msup>
                <mrow>
                    <mrow><mi mathvariant="-tex-caligraphic">D</mi></mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow>
            </msup>
        </math>
        instead of
        <math>
            <msup>
                <mrow>
                    <mrow><mi mathvariant="-tex-caligraphic">D</mi></mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow>
            </msup>
        </math>
        , the diagram change corresponds to a change of identity. Alternatively, one may keep the initial identity and justify the articulation between the constraints and χ by the subclass
        <math>
            <msup>
                <mrow>
                    <mrow><mi mathvariant="-tex-caligraphic">D</mi></mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow>
            </msup>
        </math>
        describing a partial closure that includes the constraints explicit in
        <math>
            <msup>
                <mrow>
                    <mrow><mi mathvariant="-tex-caligraphic">D</mi></mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow>
            </msup>
        </math>
        . In this case,
        <math>
            <msup>
                <mrow>
                    <mrow><mi mathvariant="-tex-caligraphic">D</mi></mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow>
            </msup>
        </math>
        is complemented by a special case,
        <math>
            <msup>
                <mrow>
                    <mrow><mi mathvariant="-tex-caligraphic">D</mi></mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow>
            </msup>
        </math>
        , that justifies the articulation between χ and constraints in
        <math>
            <msup>
                <mrow>
                    <mrow><mi mathvariant="-tex-caligraphic">D</mi></mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow>
            </msup>
        </math>
        . This justification does not guarantee that the constraints under study are always functional in
        <math>
            <msup>
                <mrow>
                    <mrow><mi mathvariant="-tex-caligraphic">D</mi></mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow>
            </msup>
